  "text": "The presented MSW model eliminates gravity wave steepening while introducing only minimal changes in other features of the SSW model. In particular, the fundamental character of the balanced, PV-controlled flow component has been retained. As noted before, the MSW model is apparently the only shallow-water-type model in which fundamental nondissipative wave-mean interaction problems of the kind investigated by [CITATION_1] can be studied numerically.",
